      "content": "In this poem, 'koso' emphasizes the noun 'mono' (things). \n\nThe adjective is **悲し** (kanashi - sad). \nIn classical Japanese, adjectives also have an Izenkei form ending in **~けれ** (~kere). \n\nTherefore, **こそ** (koso) triggers **悲しけれ** (kanashikere). This highlights the intense, undeniable sadness the poet feels upon seeing the moon.",
